ANTHRAX - UNITED KINGDOM (17): (SCOTLAND)
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Mon 22 Feb 2010
Source: BBC News [edited]
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/scotland/south_of_scotland/8528734.stm>


The total number of drug addicts who have died in Scotland after being
infected with anthrax has reached 10. The latest death was confirmed in the
NHS Fife area by Health Protection Scotland.

A fresh case has also been reported in a heroin user in the NHS Dumfries &
Galloway board area -- the 1st such incident in the region. It brings the
total number of cases in the UK to 26, with all but 2 of them in Scotland.

The outbreak began with the identification of cases in the NHS Greater
Glasgow & Clyde area in December [2009]. It has since spread to NHS board
areas in Ayrshire and Arran, Fife, Tayside, Forth Valley, Lanarkshire, and
now Dumfries & Galloway.

Health experts have said there is no way to tell if a batch of heroin is
contaminated, and no measures can be taken to make it safe. They have
advised addicts to stop taking the drug "if at all possible".

--
